The {{para|text}} parameter can be used to create customized text, in case context is required. An example is on the article [[:en:Phobos (mythology)|Phobos (mythology)]], which  contains a customized hatnote to distinguish it and "[[Phoebus]]" (a redirect of [[:en:Apollo|Apollo]]). Both links lead to topics about Greek gods, so the [[WP:NCDAB|parenthetical disambiguation]] in "Phobos (mythology)" is insufficient to disambiguate the two. Since it [[WP:HNR|is typically not preferable to link a redirect]] in a hatnote, the article "Apollo" is linked to directly and a short explanation fills in the necessary context:
